    "Like many English-speaking art scholars, he was deeply affected by the writings of Ruskin\u00a0whom he knew personally from his trips to England, and whose writing he promoted in America.": [],
    "Norton's lectures and writing focused on Italian art and civilization, paralleling the aesthetics of Ruskin and the Pre-Raphaelites, which linked esthetic purity to social reform.": [],
    "In <em>Church Building in the Middle Ages</em> he suggested that spiritual values, such as those embodied in the middle ages, led to the creation of fine art while materialism, such as that of his own age, poisoned it.": [
